56
00:03:47,801 --> 00:03:52,640
You're talking about something
that already happened,
something you experienced,

57
00:03:53,260 --> 00:03:57,920
and to help make a story more
interesting. You provide context,

58
00:03:58,850 --> 00:04:00,000
in other words,

59
00:04:00,060 --> 00:04:04,880
the background to help set the
tone of the story or to create a

60
00:04:04,881 --> 00:04:09,840
mood. Doing all of this creates a
mental picture for your listener.

61
00:04:10,230 --> 00:04:14,040
This is when we use the past
continuous tense for telling stories.

62
00:04:14,580 --> 00:04:15,920
Let me give you an example.

63
00:04:15,930 --> 00:04:20,640
Imagine you're telling someone
