76
00:05:12,870 --> 00:05:16,120
What were you doing when you
first heard the election results?

77
00:05:16,770 --> 00:05:21,279
In telling that story and providing
some background details, you might say,

78
00:05:21,870 --> 00:05:23,360
I was at an election party.

79
00:05:23,710 --> 00:05:28,120
A group of us were chatting and the music
was blaring when they first announced

80
00:05:28,121 --> 00:05:32,040
the results, there was so much noise
that we didn't hear them right away.

81
00:05:32,550 --> 00:05:35,640
This example leads me to use number two.

82
00:05:36,690 --> 00:05:41,480
We used the past continuous to
highlight overlapping events or

83
00:05:41,481 --> 00:05:45,800
interruptions. Let's start by
talking about overlapping events.

84
00:05:46,330 --> 00:05:47,161
In other words,

85
00:05:47,161 --> 00:05:52,160
when two things are happening at
the same time to show that two

86
00:05:52,161 --> 00:05:56,680
events are overlapping and to
indicate which ones started

87
00:05:56,681 --> 00:05:59,800
first, we use the past continuous.

88
00:06:00,279 --> 00:06:05,240
There are two structures we typically
use to highlight these overlapping

89
00:06:05,241 --> 00:06:05,900
events.

90
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:10,839
The first one is to use the past
continuous followed by when and the

91
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:11,880
past simple form.

92
00:06:12,589 --> 00:06:16,800
I was chatting with friends
when they announced the results

93
00:06:17,410 --> 00:06:20,920
or we could reverse that when
they announced the results.

94
00:06:20,950 --> 00:06:22,320
I was chatting with friends.

95
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:27,520
In both cases the use of the
past continuous highlights,

96
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,160
which of the two events started first.

97
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:36,760
The second structure we can
use is to include a specific

98
00:06:36,761 --> 00:06:41,400
indication of time that
highlights something was

99
00:06:41,401 --> 00:06:44,480
happening before and after. For example,

100
00:06:44,730 --> 00:06:49,160
at midnight at 7:00 PM in September

101
00:06:50,290 --> 00:06:51,720
by the age of 12.

102
00:06:52,339 --> 00:06:57,320
Let me give you a few examples of how
